-- T. Rowe's Rogers to step down as manager of $30 bln equity fund 
-- By Ross Kerber
-- Tue Jun 03, 2014 10:31AM EDT
-- None



BOSTON, June 3 (Reuters) - Baltimore asset manager T. Rowe Price Group Inc <TROW.O> said Brian Rogers will step down as manager of its $30 billion Equity Income <PRFDX.O> fund in October 2015 and hand over the reins to John Linehan.

Rogers will remain the company's chief investment officer and chairman of its board of directors, T. Rowe Price said on Tuesday.